    "But in order for Anscombe's pluralism about agential causes to avoid overinclusive answers to the question 'what does the agent do?",
    "', we must be able to say what about the position of someone who can cite motives and intentions enables that person to attribute actions to agents; and in order to do justice to Anscombe's version of the thesis that multiple action descriptions needn't entail multiple actions, we need to say what Anscombe could mean by 'the same action' if actions are not to be identified with particular bodily movements.",
    "We need to articulate an Anscombean alternative to the A-D Principle.",
    "Here an analogy might be useful.",
    "15 One way to think about ordinary objects is as mereological sums of their most fundamental parts."
